HEADWORD: Gazingstock
<hw>Gaz"ing*stock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person or
thing gazed at with scorn or abhorrence; an object of curiosity or
contempt.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

